<topic id="dcpp_flagging_the_content">
    <title>Flagging Content</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm product="author developer editor authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            ><ph keyref="pdf-html5-transformation"/>
          <indexterm>Flagging content</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="pdf-css ope">Flagging content</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <body>
        <p>In DITA, you can mark certain content to flag it or draw attention to it. This is done by
      defining a flag in a DITAVAL file. </p>
    <p>You can attach the DITAVAL file to the DITA map using the <xmlelement>ditavalref</xmlelement>
      element in the map, or by specifying it in the <codeph>args.filter</codeph> transformation
      parameter.</p>
    <p>In the following example, all the elements that have the attribute <xmlatt>product</xmlatt>
      set to <codeph>YourProd</codeph> is flagged to have a purple background:</p>
    <codeblock outputclass="language-xml">&lt;val>
...
   &lt;prop action="flag" att="product" val="YourProd" backcolor="purple"/>
...
&lt;/val></codeblock>
    </body>
